00e6r]], the late-goal specialist, to give them the lead with his 100th goal for the club. They could not add to their one-goal advantage, despite West Brom having to play with ten men with [[Derek McInnes]] being sent off for two bookings, the second for a foul on [[Nicky Butt]] in the 64th minute, but held on to begin the season with victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/2196586.stm |title=Solskjaer saves Man Utd |publisher=BBC |work=BBC Sport |date=17 August 2002 |accessdate=22 December 2008 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Opponents\n!H/A\n!Result<br />F\u2013A\n!Scorers\n!Attendance\n!League<br />position\n|- bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"\n|17 August 2002\n|[[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]\n|H\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2196586.stm 1\u20130]\n|[[Ole Gunnar Solskj\u00e6r|Solskj\u00e6r]] 78'\n|67,645\n|7th\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\"\n|23 August 2002\n|[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|A\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2208797.stm 2\u20132]\n|[[David Beckham|Beckham]] 26', [[Ryan Giggs|Giggs]] 66'\n|41,541\n|7th\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffffdd\"\n|31 August 2002\n|[[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]\n|A\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2224543.stm 1\u20131]\n|[[Ryan Giggs|Giggs]] 7'\n|47,586\n|8th\n|- bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"\n|3 September 2002\n|[[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]\n|H\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2230725.stm 1\u20130]\n|[[Ruud van Nistelrooy|Van Nistelrooy]] 28' ([[Penalty kick (association football)|pen.]])\n|67,464\n|4th\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"\n|11 September 2002\n|[[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]]\n|H\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2245927.stm 0\u20131]\n|\n|67,623\n|7th\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"\n|14 September 2002\n|[[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]]\n|A\n|[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/2254743.stm 0\u20131]\n|\n|39,622\n|10th\n|- bgcolo