{"title_page": "Men of Steel (song)", "text_new": "{{1990s-hip-hop-song-stub}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Men of Steel\n| cover      = Men of Steel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]] and [[KRS-One]]\n| album      = [[Steel (soundtrack)]]\n| released   = July 29, 1997\n| format     = [[7\" single]], [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1997\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Rap music|Rap]]\n| length     = 4:35\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]], [[Qwest Records]]\n| writer     = [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[KRS-One]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]]\n| producer   = [[Trackmasters]]\n| chronology = [[Shaquille O'Neal]]\n| prev_title = [[Strait Playin']]\n| prev_year  = 1997\n| next_title = [[The Way It's Goin' Down]]\n| next_year  = 1998\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Ice Cube]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[The World Is Mine (Ice Cube song)|The World Is Mine]]\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = [[We Be Clubbin']]\n | next_year  = 1997\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[B-Real]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Hit 'Em High (The Monstars' Anthem)]]\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = \"[[Dr. Greenthumb]]\" (with [[Cypress Hill]])\n | next_year  = 1998\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[KRS-One]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = A Friend\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = 5 Boroughs\n | next_year  = 1998\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Men of Steel'''\" is a single by the rappers [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]] and [[KRS-One]] from the [[Steel (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] to the movie ''[[Steel (1997 film)|Steel]]''.\n\nIt was the only single released from the soundtrack. Released in 1997 for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]/[[Qwest Records]], it was produced by the [[Trackmasters]] (then known as Poke & Tone). The five [[rapping|rappers]] wrote their own verses. \n\n\"Men of Steel\" was a success, reaching #87 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], #10 on the [[Hot Rap Singles]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/shaquille-oneal/chart-history/RAP/song/51824|title=Shaquille O'Neal|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> and #53 on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks]].\n\n==Single track listing==\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (Album Version) - 4:35\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (Instrumental) - 4:35\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (A Cappella) - 4:31\n\n{{Ice Cube}}\n{{Shaquille O'Neal}}\n\n[[Category:1997 singles]]\n[[Category:Ice Cube songs]]\n[[Category:KRS-One songs]]\n[[Category:Shaquille O'Neal songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ice Cube]]\n[[Category:Warner Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Shaquille O'Neal]]\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Trackmasters]]\n[[Category:Songs written by KRS-One]]\n[[Category:Songs written by B-Real]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Men of Steel\n| cover      = Men of Steel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]] and [[KRS-One]]\n| album      = [[Steel (soundtrack)]]\n| released   = July 29, 1997\n| format     = [[7\" single]], [[CD single]]\n| recorded   = 1997\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Rap music|Rap]]\n| length     = 4:35\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]], [[Qwest Records]]\n| writer     = [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[KRS-One]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]]\n| producer   = [[Trackmasters]]\n| chronology = [[Shaquille O'Neal]]\n| prev_title = [[Strait Playin']]\n| prev_year  = 1997\n| next_title = [[The Way It's Goin' Down]]\n| next_year  = 1998\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Ice Cube]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[The World Is Mine (Ice Cube song)|The World Is Mine]]\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = [[We Be Clubbin']]\n | next_year  = 1997\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[B-Real]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Hit 'Em High (The Monstars' Anthem)]]\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = \"[[Dr. Greenthumb]]\" (with [[Cypress Hill]])\n | next_year  = 1998\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[KRS-One]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = A Friend\n | prev_year  = 1997\n | title      = Men of Steel\n | year       = 1997\n | next_title = 5 Boroughs\n | next_year  = 1998\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Men of Steel'''\" is a single by the rappers [[Shaquille O'Neal]], [[Ice Cube]], [[B-Real]], [[Peter Gunz]] and [[KRS-One]] from the [[Steel (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] to the movie ''[[Steel (1997 film)|Steel]]''.\n\n\"Men of Steel\" was the only single released from the soundtrack. It was released in 1997 for [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]/[[Qwest Records]] and was produced by the [[Trackmasters]] (then known as Poke & Tone). The five [[rapping|rappers]] wrote their own verses. \"Men of Steel\" was a success, reaching #87 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], #10 on the [[Hot Rap Singles]] and #53 on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks]].\n\n==Single track listing==\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (Album Version) - 4:35\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (Instrumental) - 4:35\n#\"Men Of Steel\" (A Cappella) - 4:31\n\n{{Ice Cube}}\n{{Shaquille O'Neal}}\n\n[[Category:1997 singles]]\n[[Category:Ice Cube songs]]\n[[Category:KRS-One songs]]\n[[Category:Shaquille O'Neal songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Ice Cube]]\n[[Category:Warner Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Shaquille O'Neal]]\n[[Category:1997 songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Trackmasters]]\n[[Category:Songs written by KRS-One]]\n[[Category:Songs written 